---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Rohith Yadla is a platform engineer building infrastructure at scale for the BC Government. Creator of Cortex." />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <article class="about">
        <div class="about-inner">
          <header class="about-header">
            <h1>About</h1>
          </header>

          <div class="about-content">
            <section>
              <p class="intro">
                I'm Rohith Yadla, a platform engineer based in British Columbia, Canada. I build and operate the infrastructure that teams depend on to ship software. My work sits at the intersection of Kubernetes, automation, and developer experience.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>What I do</h2>
              <p>
                I design and manage container platforms on OpenShift and Kubernetes. I build CI/CD pipelines, configure GitOps workflows, set up observability stacks, and generally make sure that developers can deploy with confidence and ops teams can sleep at night.
              </p>
              <p>
                Recently, I've been deep in AI-assisted operations. Using Claude Code, MCP servers, and custom memory systems to build tooling that makes infrastructure work faster and more reliable.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Career highlights</h2>
              <ul class="highlights">
                <li>Platform Engineer at the BC Government, supporting critical public services</li>
                <li>14 production applications running across 3 OpenShift clusters (Silver, Gold, Emerald)</li>
                <li>Built and maintained Helm charts, Tekton pipelines, and ArgoCD deployments at scale</li>
                <li>Designed multi-cluster namespace strategies and production readiness frameworks</li>
                <li>Early adopter of AI-powered DevOps workflows with Claude Code and MCP</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>The Cortex story</h2>
              <p>
                Cortex is my personal knowledge system -- a structured memory layer that sits behind my AI tooling. It tracks decisions, architecture patterns, operational playbooks, and context across every project I work on.
              </p>
              <p>
                The idea is simple: infrastructure work generates enormous amounts of context. Cortex captures that context and makes it available exactly when it's needed. It's how I maintain clarity across clusters, namespaces, and dozens of applications without losing signal in the noise.
              </p>
              <p>
                I'm building Cortex in the open and writing about it on this blog.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Why Yarova</h2>
              <p>
                Yarova is the name behind my consulting and writing practice. It exists because I believe the best infrastructure knowledge shouldn't be locked inside one organization. The problems teams face with Kubernetes, CI/CD, and platform engineering are universal. The solutions should be shared.
              </p>
              <p>
                Through Yarova, I offer consulting, coaching, and AI automation services to teams that want to level up their infrastructure game. If that sounds like your team, <a href="/services">take a look at what I offer</a> or <a href="mailto:rohith@yarova.ca">send me an email</a>.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="connect">
              <h2>Connect</h2>
              <ul class="social-list">
                <li><a href="https://github.com/AceYarova" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://linkedin.com/in/rohithyadla" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://twitter.com/AceYarova" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twitter / X</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://bsky.app/profile/yarova.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bluesky</a></li>
                <li><a href="mailto:rohith@yarova.ca">rohith@yarova.ca</a></li>
              </ul>
            </section>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  main {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-inner {
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-6);
  }

  .about-header {
    padding: var(--space-20) 0 var(--space-8);
  }

  .about-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .about-content section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .about-content h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .about-content p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: var(--text-lg) !important;
    color: var(--text-primary) !important;
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .about-content a {
    color: var(--color-amber);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .about-content a:hover {
    color: var(--color-amber-hover);
  }

  .highlights {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .highlights li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }

  .highlights li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 10px;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    background: var(--color-amber);
  }

  .social-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .social-list a {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about-header {
      padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-6);
    }

    .about-header h1 {
      font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    }
  }
</style>
